733422f-a.title: Transportation - Elevated - Steam-drawn trains.
733422f-a.text:
The early steam drawn elevated trains, as seen at 110th Street and
Columbus Ave., in Manhattan.
About 1890.
New York Edison Co.
Neg #429
733422f-a.folder: 110th Street and Columbus Avenue, Manhattan, N.Y.

718120f-a.text:
Cathedral Parkway (West 110th Street), west from and including Columbus Ave. In the foreground are the Elevated lines as they turn to go south on Columbus Ave.
October 25, 1927.
F. L. Speyer
